Product API
 Node.js API built with Express and MongoDB. It supports basic CRUD operations, allowing you to create, read, update, and delete products.


Repository: https://github.com/noriega146/SBA-319---MongoDB-Database-Application

API Endpoints
GET /api/products

Retrieves all products.
Response: 200 OK with an array of products.
GET /api/products/

Retrieves a product by its ID.
Response: 200 OK with the product ID.
POST /api/products

Creates a new product.
Request Body: JSON with the product info.
Response: 201 Created with the new product.
PUT /api/products/

Updates an existing product by its ID.
Request Body: JSON with updated product details.
Response: 200 OK with the updated product.
DELETE /api/products/

Deletes a product by its ID.
Response: 204 No Content on success.

API Client: Used Insomnia tool to test the API.Installation
Create a Product: Sent a POST request with product details.
Get All Products: Sent a GET request to fetch all products.
Update a Product: Sent a PUT request with updated product data.
Delete a Product: Sent a DELETE request with the product ID.
